# 04 Encryption and Key Management

## Intent
Ensure confidentiality/integrity for personal data and PHI through strong cryptography.

## Mandatory
- TLS everywhere for service-to-service and client-to-service traffic.
- Encrypt data at rest for databases, object stores, queues, and backups.
- Use managed KMS/HSM-backed keys; no app-managed raw master keys.
- Separate keys by environment and sensitivity class.
- Define key rotation schedule and emergency rotation playbook.

## Operational Rules
- Access to key operations must be least-privilege and auditable.
- Secret material must come from managed secret stores, never source control.

## Release Blockers
- Any plaintext sensitive transport path.
- Missing key ownership/rotation metadata.
